 The goal of this study is to test the efficacy of an algorithm we previously created to adjust Continuous positive airway pressure (CPAP) when a mask interface is switched from a nasal to a full face.

 Subjects will currently have a moderate to severe Apnea-hypopnea index (AHI - The Apnea-Hypopnea Index or Apnoea-Hypopnoea Index (AHI) is an index used to indicate the severity of sleep apnea.

 It is represented by the number of apnea and hypopnea events per hour of sleep).

